&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#%E9%A1%8C%E7%9B%AE%E6%95%98%E8%BF%B0&#34;&gt;amateurs&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;adj. 業餘愛好的，非職業的&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br&gt;
 Taking part in an activity for pleasure, not as a job.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;ex.&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;He was an amateur singer until the age of 40, when he turned professional.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;n. 外行；粗通（某一行）的人&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br&gt;
 Someone who does not have much skill in what they do.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;ex.&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;I won’t be giving them any more work - they’re a bunch of amateurs.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
